ğŸ› ï¸ Setup Instructions

 1. Clone the Repository

git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/<your-repo>.git
cd <your-repo>

2. Configure Jenkins
Install Jenkins (Docker recommended)

Install plugins: Pipeline, Docker Pipeline, SonarQube Scanner, Git

Add credentials:

DockerHub (docker-cred)

SonarQube server (sonar)

Create a Jenkins job pointing to this repo

3. Pull Required Docker Images

docker pull sonarqube:latest
docker pull aquasec/trivy:latest
docker pull nurdism/neko:firefox

ğŸ§ª Pipeline Stages
Git Checkout â€“ Pulls latest code from GitHub

Trivy Filesystem Scan â€“ Scans source files for vulnerabilities

SonarQube Analysis â€“ Runs static code analysis

Docker Build & Tag â€“ Builds image from Dockerfile

Trivy Docker Scan â€“ Scans built image for vulnerabilities

Docker Push â€“ Pushes image to DockerHub

Deploy â€“ Uses Docker Compose to run the container

ğŸ” Login Credentials
By default, login is disabled for public access. To enable password protection, add these to docker-compose.yaml:

environment:
  NEKO_PASSWORD: yourpassword
  NEKO_PASSWORD_ADMIN: youradminpassword

ğŸ“¦ Deployment
docker-compose down -v
docker-compose up -d --build
Access the app at: http://localhost:8081

ğŸ§¹ Cleanup
bash
docker image prune -f
docker-compose down -v
